The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), will visit Zamfara State on Thursday (today). The state governor, Bello Matawalle, disclosed during an emergency meeting with all political appointees at the Government House’s Council Chamber on Tuesday evening. According to the governor, the main purpose of the President’s visit is to commiserate with his administration over the recent bandits’ attacks in Anka and Bukkuyum Local Government Areas which claimed many lives. Matawalle said, “All is set to ensure the President is received successfully. “I want to inform all the good people of Zamfara State that the Commander-in-Chief of the Federal republic of Nigeria will come to Zamfara on Thursday specifically for a condolence visit over the recent banditry in Anka and Bukkuyum Local Government Areas of the state.” The governor urged the people of the state to remain law-abiding during the President’s visit.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com